@zack Instead you are trusting some person to put some data that may or may not be related to reality onto the blockchain.
There is no cryptoeconomic guarantees that the data on-chain has any relationship to reality. An how does that differ from Amoveo? You've stated that you can manually "hard update" to stop an oracle "about to lie", what "cryptoeconomic guarantees" exist to ensure that what you do "may or may not be related to reality"? This is an important distinction, so I'll keep asking until you answer....

